    dc:date "2006" ;
    dc:title "Leonardesmus injucundus, n. gen., n. sp., an aromatic, small-bodied milliped from Washington State, U. S. A., and a revised account of the family Nearctodesmidae (Polydesmida)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058815>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058819>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058825>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058823>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058817> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058815>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Leonardesmus injucundus syntype from Grays Harbor Co., Washington. Photo by W. P. Leonard." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5058815/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058819>
    dc:description "FIGURES 4–6. 4, SEM photo of head and segments 1–7 of male syntype, ventrolateral view from left side; 5, midbody tergite of poriferous segment of the same, dorsal view; 6, left ozopore on caudolateral paranotal corner of the same, dorsal view. Magnifications indicated on scale lines." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5058819/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058825>
    dc:description "FIGURES 10–12. 10, Left gonopod of male syntype, medial view; 11, the same, lateral view; 12, Left cyphopod of female syntype, caudal view. Scale lines for figs 10–11 and fig. 12 = 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5058825/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058823>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7–9. 7, SEM photo of left gonopod of male syntype, sublateral view; 8, the same, submedial view; 9, the same, subventral view. Magnifications indicated on scale lines." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5058823/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5058817>
    dc:description "FIGURES 2–3. 2, Distribution of the Nearctodesmidae. The dot in southcentral British Columbia represents the allopatric population of Nearctodesmus insulanus in the Shuswap Region; those in California, Nevada, and Arizona, some covering two closely proximate sites, represent known or published localities for the southwestern \"micro­nearctodesmids.\" 3, Known occurrences of Leonardesmus and L. injucundus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5058817/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

